Container returned by create_pipeline. Holds the assembled CapabilityManager, JobQueue, and a bindings dict mapping capability names to CapabilityBinding views for the capabilities that loaded successfully. Implements async context-manager semantics for ergonomic teardown:
async with create_pipeline(capabilities=["whisper", "sys-mon"]) as pipe:
    result = await pipe.bindings["whisper"].execute_async(audio=path)
The context-manager exit calls queue.stop() + manager.unload_all().




